TITLE: Creating an Azure AD User - Terraform - Terraform
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to define a new Azure AD user using the `azuread_user` resource in a Terraform configuration. It sets key properties such as user principal name, display name, mail nickname, and password. Dependencies include the AzureAD Terraform provider and required API permissions or directory/app roles. Parameters like `user_principal_name` and `password` are required; optional fields can customize the user's identity and account settings. The configuration creates an Azure AD user and expects standard Terraform apply workflow for provisioning.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/terraform-provider-azuread/blob/main/docs/resources/user.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Terraform
CODE:
```
resource "azuread_user" "example" {
  user_principal_name = "jdoe@hashicorp.com"
  display_name        = "J. Doe"
  mail_nickname       = "jdoe"
  password            = "SecretP@sswd99!"
}
```

