TITLE: Defining HCL Numeric Literal Syntax using EBNF
DESCRIPTION: Specifies the EBNF grammar for numeric literals in HCL. A numeric literal represents a real number and consists of a mandatory decimal integer part, an optional fractional part (starting with '.'), and an optional exponent part (starting with 'e' or 'E').
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/terraform-provider-azuread/blob/main/vendor/github.com/hashicorp/hcl/v2/hclsyntax/spec.md#2025-04-23_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: ebnf
CODE:
```
NumericLit = decimal+ ("." decimal+)? (expmark decimal+)?;
decimal    = '0' .. '9';
expmark    = ('e' | 'E') ("+" | "-")?;
```

