TITLE: Defining Collection Value Syntax (Tuples and Objects) in EBNF
DESCRIPTION: Provides the EBNF grammar for constructing tuple (`[...]`) and object (`{...}`) collection values in HCL. It specifies how elements are defined using expressions and separated by commas or newlines. For objects, elements consist of a key (Identifier or Expression) and a value (Expression), separated by '=' or ':'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/terraform-provider-azuread/blob/main/vendor/github.com/hashicorp/hcl/v2/hclsyntax/spec.md#2025-04-23_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: ebnf
CODE:
```
CollectionValue = tuple | object;
tuple = "[" (
    (Expression (( "," | Newline) Expression)* ","?)?
) "]";
object = "{" (
    (objectelem (( "," | Newline) objectelem)* ","?)?
) "}";
objectelem = (Identifier | Expression) ("=" | ":") Expression;
```

