TITLE: Defining Operations Syntax in EBNF
DESCRIPTION: EBNF grammar for unary and binary operations in HCL, including comparison, arithmetic, and logical operators. Includes operator precedence levels where higher values bind tighter.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hashicorp/terraform-provider-azuread/blob/main/vendor/github.com/hashicorp/hcl/v2/hclsyntax/spec.md#2025-04-23_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: ebnf
CODE:
```
Operation = unaryOp | binaryOp;
unaryOp = ("-" | "!") ExprTerm;
binaryOp = ExprTerm binaryOperator ExprTerm;
binaryOperator = compareOperator | arithmeticOperator | logicOperator;
compareOperator = "==" | "!=" | "<" | ">" | "<=" | ">=";
arithmeticOperator = "+" | "-" | "*" | "/" | "%";
logicOperator = "&&" | "||";
```

